Sentencas: CuCo2O4-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 (GDC) composite was investigated as a potentially promising cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: CuCo2O4-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 as a Potential Cathode Material for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The CuCo2O4-GDC composite cathodes were characterized via X-ray diffraction, scanning electron microscopy and thermal expansion.
Titulo: CuCo2O4-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 as a Potential Cathode Material for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: CuCo2O4-GDC composites exhibited a good chemical compatibility and thermal compatibility for each composition.
Titulo: CuCo2O4-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 as a Potential Cathode Material for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Introduction of the GDC nanoparticles increased the length of TPBs and enhanced the electrochemical activities of the CuCo2O4-GDC composite cathode.
Titulo: CuCo2O4-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 as a Potential Cathode Material for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance with addition of 60 wt.% of GDC showed the least value of 0.09 cm(2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: CuCo2O4-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 as a Potential Cathode Material for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results demonstrated that CuCo2O4-GDC composite would be a promising cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
